35:47.012 --> 35:49.246
Whenever you like.

35:53.351 --> 35:55.785
<i> I felt that I had to speak</i>

35:55.787 --> 35:59.656
<i> to the families of our country</i>
<i> about grief.</i>

36:06.430 --> 36:10.767
<i> A plea not to leave</i>
<i> the children isolated</i>

36:10.769 --> 36:13.270
<i> and at the mercy</i>
<i> of their own fantasies</i>

36:13.272 --> 36:15.605
<i> of loss and destruction.</i>

36:18.943 --> 36:23.113
<i> Children have</i>
<i> very deep feelings</i>

36:23.115 --> 36:25.515
<i> just the way parents do,</i>

36:25.517 --> 36:29.986
<i> just the way everybody does.</i>

36:29.988 --> 36:36.159
<i> And our striving</i>
<i> to understand those feelings</i>

36:36.161 --> 36:39.863
and to better respond to them

36:39.865 --> 36:44.868
is what I feel is a most
important task in our world.

36:50.876 --> 36:54.077
<i> He realized</i>
<i> that if he really wanted</i>

36:54.079 --> 36:57.747
to communicate,
the most important thing

36:57.749 --> 36:59.549
is to listen.

36:59.551 --> 37:01.351
'Cause there's so many people
who will just

37:01.353 --> 37:05.855
lump 'em all together and say,
"hey, kids, come along.

37:05.857 --> 37:07.724
We'll see the next cartoon."

37:07.726 --> 37:09.826
And they couldn't
care less about

37:09.828 --> 37:12.829
what that cartoon
is saying to the child

37:12.831 --> 37:15.565
about such things
as human dignity.

37:27.379 --> 37:28.678
<i> Remember what was happening</i>

37:28.680 --> 37:30.847
<i> for children's television.</i>

37:30.849 --> 37:32.515
<i> It was speeding up.</i>

37:32.517 --> 37:35.852
<i> Fred was pretty radical</i>
<i> in television for that day</i>

37:35.854 --> 37:37.854
<i> in that he used time</i>

37:37.856 --> 37:39.422
totally differently.

37:45.463 --> 37:48.932
<i> To Fred, silence</i>

37:48.934 --> 37:50.867
was his delight.

38:04.982 --> 38:08.051
<i> Fred took</i>
<i> an egg timer and said,</i>

38:08.053 --> 38:10.220
