Feeling is dead for me in here.

48:38.282 --> 48:41.684
<i> He was incredibly open.</i>

48:41.686 --> 48:44.120
He was scarily open.

48:46.456 --> 48:48.457
<i> He wanted to speak to adults.</i>

48:48.459 --> 48:50.459
<i> He kind of put</i>
<i> the puppets away.</i>

48:50.461 --> 48:53.296
But have you watched
some of these?

48:54.298 --> 48:57.033
The feeling that...

48:57.035 --> 49:01.704
This instrument is a place,

49:01.706 --> 49:05.942
that it is a country,

49:05.944 --> 49:10.046
that it's somewhere that you go

49:10.048 --> 49:13.015
to say something.

49:17.087 --> 49:18.921
What... what does this

49:18.923 --> 49:21.023
have to do with our world?

49:22.426 --> 49:25.995
I don't know any store
that's like this.

49:25.997 --> 49:29.565
Any television program
that's like this.

49:29.567 --> 49:31.534
A flower is like this.

49:32.669 --> 49:34.737
A child is like this.

49:34.739 --> 49:37.773
<i> Nobody but Fred</i>
<i> would have thought</i>

49:37.775 --> 49:40.176
<i> of doing that for adults.</i>

49:40.178 --> 49:42.244
Take number 19.

49:42.246 --> 49:45.081
Thank you for your poems
and your thoughts

49:45.083 --> 49:48.117
about loving poetry and music.

49:48.119 --> 49:51.420
You really inspired us
to make this program.

49:51.422 --> 49:54.190
I'll be with you next time.

49:54.192 --> 49:56.325
<i> But he wasn't making</i>

49:56.327 --> 49:58.260
the kind of connections
with adults on television

49:58.262 --> 50:00.496
that he thought
he might be able to make.

50:04.534 --> 50:07.269
<i> I remember opening the paper</i>

50:07.271 --> 50:09.438
<i> and reading about a child</i>

50:09.440 --> 50:12.441
jumping off a roof
with a towel around his neck

50:12.443 --> 50:15.077
<i> because he was</i>
<i> playing superman.</i>

50:17.280 --> 50:19.715
<i> And there had been a lot</i>
<i> of stories like that.</i>

50:19.717 --> 50:22.952
<i> Some children died</i>
<i> because of the injuries.</i>

50:22.954 --> 50:24.387
<i> I read it to Fred.</i>

50:24.389 --> 50:27.023
<i> It hit him, because he thought</i>
<i> he had covered</i>

50:27.025 --> 50:30.960
<i> all that there was to say</i>
<i> in child development,</i>

50:30.962 --> 50:33.195
but this was new.

50:33.197 --> 50:35.464
<i>Fred didn't become angry a lot,</i>

50:35.466 --> 50:38.401
<i> but he just became so angry</i>
<i> about the fact</i>

50:38.403 --> 50:40.970
<i> that people would mislead</i>
<i> a small child.</i>

50:40.972 --> 50:44.573
<i> And angry</i>
<i> that it was his medium</i>

50:44.575 --> 50:46.308
that was doing this.

50:51.648 --> 50:52.782
Yeah, superman.

50:55.752 --> 50:59.321
I am tired of hearing people
who have long ago

50:59.323 --> 51:02.658
set aside the concerns
of childhood,

51:02.660 --> 51:06.395
<i> telling everybody</i>
<i> what children really need.</i>

51:06.397 --> 51:09.065
I'll tell you
what children need.

51:10.333 --> 51:13.736
They need adults
who will protect them

51:13.738 --> 51:17.940
from the ever-ready molders
of their world.

51:20.611 --> 51:23.512
<i> That was the moment Fred said,</i>

51:23.514 --> 51:26.382
"i wonder if we could do
a week on superheroes,

51:26.384 --> 51:30.152
<i> talking about</i>
<i> the pretend-ness of it."</i>

51:31.021 --> 51:32.588
<i> Very quickly,</i>

51:32.590 --> 51:36.592
<i> we came back with the show. </i>

51:43.767 --> 51:44.700
Mm-hmm.

51:44.702 --> 51:46.402
<i> Uh, careful, Ana.</i>

51:46.404 --> 51:48.437
-I don't want you to...
-I think I'm flying.

51:48.439 --> 51:50.973
-I am! I'm flying!
-No, you're falling!

51:50.975 --> 51:52.908
What is going on here?

51:52.910 --> 51:55.811
Oh, Ana was trying to fly.

51:55.813 --> 51:57.880
I was using my super-skirt,

51:57.882 --> 51:59.548
and I was going
through the air.

51:59.550 --> 52:02.952
Yes, but you were going down,
and you might have gotten hurt.

52:02.954 --> 52:04.420
That's right, Ana.

52:04.422 --> 52:06.589
You have to be really careful

52:06.591 --> 52:08.491
with super-things.

52:08.493 --> 52:12.561
<i> He was cool with every kid.</i>

52:12.563 --> 52:15.397
That's the whole thing.
I mean, there were little...

52:15.399 --> 52:17.299
Kids that were...
They were little bastards.

52:17.301 --> 52:20.336
They were just rowdy,
and Fred never said,

52:20.338 --> 52:22.605
"this kid's a dick.
Get him out of here."

52:22.607 --> 52:25.074
You know, I mean,
i sure would've.

52:25.076 --> 52:27.610
<i> Fred used to say</i>

52:27.612 --> 52:30.646
that the outside world
of children's lives

52:30.648 --> 52:33.349
has changed,
but their insides haven't.

52:33.351 --> 52:37.086
<i> He realized that his work</i>
<i> wasn't through.</i>

