Some people
get married, and after a while,

52:58.376 --> 53:00.376
they're so unhappy
with each other

53:00.378 --> 53:03.112
that they don't want
to be married anymore.

53:03.114 --> 53:05.447
On children getting lost.

53:05.449 --> 53:08.284
Man, that's guts.

53:10.320 --> 53:12.988
Help! Help, help!

53:12.990 --> 53:14.657
Help, please, everybody!

53:24.901 --> 53:29.405
<i> There's a piece of paper</i>
<i> that I accidentally ran into.</i>

53:31.875 --> 53:34.910
<i> And he typed in this little</i>
<i> sheet of paper</i>

53:34.912 --> 53:38.314
<i> about how he couldn't do it,</i>

53:38.316 --> 53:40.716
that he didn't think
he was up to the task.

53:41.751 --> 53:43.719
<i> "Am I kidding myself</i>

53:43.721 --> 53:46.655
<i> "that I'm able to write</i>
<i> a script again?</i>

53:46.657 --> 53:49.658
<i> "Am I really just</i>
<i> whistling Dixie?</i>

53:49.660 --> 53:51.660
<i> "I wonder.</i>

53:51.662 --> 53:57.032
<i> "If I don't get down to it,</i>
<i> I'll never really know.</i>

53:57.034 --> 53:59.435
<i> "Why don't I trust myself?</i>

53:59.437 --> 54:02.171
<i> "After all these years,</i>

54:02.173 --> 54:06.709
<i> "it's just as bad as ever.</i>

54:06.711 --> 54:10.412
<i> "The hour cometh, and now</i>
<i> is when I've got to do it.</i>

54:10.414 --> 54:14.016
<i> "Get to it, Fred. Get to it.</i>

54:14.018 --> 54:18.454
<i> "But don't let anybody</i>
<i> ever tell anybody else</i>

54:18.456 --> 54:20.289
<i> "that it was easy.</i>

54:20.291 --> 54:22.024
<i> It wasn't."</i>

54:27.964 --> 54:30.733
<i> The time that I was with him</i>

54:30.735 --> 54:34.069
<i> going on a New York City</i>
<i> subway, all the children</i>

54:34.071 --> 54:35.971
in that crowded subway car

54:35.973 --> 54:39.041
<i> began singing</i>
<i> the</i> neighborhood <i> song.</i>

54:51.722 --> 54:54.890
<i> He might as well</i>
<i> have been an animated figure</i>

54:54.892 --> 54:57.126
<i> stepped into real life.</i>

54:57.128 --> 54:58.961
Could I try that?

54:59.964 --> 55:01.063
I brought my skates with me.

55:01.065 --> 55:02.064
I can try.

55:02.066 --> 55:04.566
Whoa.

55:08.906 --> 55:10.906
-What else do you like to do?
-Moonwalk.

55:10.908 --> 55:14.243
- Moonwalk?
- You got it. Yeah.

55:14.245 --> 55:15.811
<i> People thought he was</i>

55:15.813 --> 55:18.314
<i> such an important</i>
<i> American figure,</i>

55:18.316 --> 55:20.015
<i> they wanted him to speak out</i>

55:20.017 --> 55:21.784
on the issues of the day.

55:21.786 --> 55:24.420
<i> And so Fred grew</i>
<i> pretty comfortably</i>

55:24.422 --> 55:25.821
<i> into more of a public role.</i>

55:25.823 --> 55:27.956
You know, the earth is a name

55:27.958 --> 55:30.926
for the place
where everybody lives.

55:30.928 --> 55:32.361
And the moon

55:32.363 --> 55:34.530
<i> is the name for the place</i>

55:34.532 --> 55:36.632
<i> where the astronauts go.</i>

55:36.634 --> 55:39.301
<i> Every time we went through</i>

55:39.303 --> 55:41.503
a national
or international tragedy,

55:41.505 --> 55:44.440
<i> my impulse was always</i>
<i> to call Fred</i>

55:44.442 --> 55:45.708
<i> and put him on the radio.</i>

55:45.710 --> 55:47.776
<i>What shall we tell our children</i>

55:47.778 --> 55:50.446
<i> about the things</i>
<i> that are in the news</i>

55:50.448 --> 55:52.448
<i> that seem so difficult,</i>
<i> so tragic?</i>

55:52.450 --> 55:53.949
<i> Pilot Mike Smith,</i>

55:53.951 --> 55:56.719
<i> followed by christa mcauliffe,</i>
<i> teacher in space.</i>

55:56.721 --> 55:58.387
<i> Christa has been rehearsing</i>

55:58.389 --> 56:00.389
<i> the lessons she'll teach</i>
<i> from space.</i>

56:00.391 --> 56:01.990
Good morning.

56:01.992 --> 56:04.626
This is christa mcauliffe,
live from the <i> challenger.</i>

56:04.628 --> 56:06.362
<i> The lessons will be seen</i>

56:06.364 --> 56:08.130
<i> nationwide</i>
<i> on public television.</i>

56:08.132 --> 56:11.166
Five, four, three...

56:11.168 --> 56:13.402
<i> Two, one...</i>

56:13.404 --> 56:14.803
<i> And liftoff!</i>

56:14.805 --> 56:18.307
<i> Liftoff of the 25th</i>
<i> space shuttle mission,</i>

56:18.309 --> 56:19.808
<i> and it has cleared the tower.</i>

56:19.810 --> 56:21.543
Challenger,
<i> go at throttle up.</i>

56:21.545 --> 56:23.879
<i> Roger. Go at throttle up.</i>

56:30.320 --> 56:32.421
God, no!

56:36.092 --> 56:38.694
<i> How do we put it to children</i>

56:38.696 --> 56:40.996
<i> so they will understand?</i>

56:44.501 --> 56:48.337
<i> And part of Fred's answer</i>
<i> was always to tell children</i>

56:48.339 --> 56:51.673
<i> that we, the parents,</i>
<i> would take care of them.</i>

56:52.942 --> 56:55.344
Sometimes I found that
a difficult message myself

56:55.346 --> 56:57.379
as the parent of a young child.

56:57.381 --> 56:59.081
Sometimes I felt I was lying.

56:59.083 --> 57:01.016
I knew that there were things
in this world

57:01.018 --> 57:03.118
that I couldn't protect
my child from.

57:06.089 --> 57:08.524
<i> Sometimes we need to struggle</i>

57:08.526 --> 57:13.462
<i> with a tragedy</i>
<i> to feel the gravity of love.</i>

57:13.464 --> 57:17.766
Love is what keeps us
together and afloat.

57:30.581 --> 57:34.149
<i> You know, it must</i>
<i> be tough to be Fred Rogers...</i>

57:35.385 --> 57:39.588
...with your mission in mind

57:39.590 --> 57:41.657
and then to have parodies.

58:02.079 --> 58:04.580
<i> Eddie Murphy did that</i>

58:04.582 --> 58:06.415
mister Robinson's neighborhood,

58:06.417 --> 58:08.617
<i> and I remember meeting him,</i>

58:08.619 --> 58:10.519
<i> and he just threw his arms</i>
<i> around me</i>

58:10.521 --> 58:12.521
<i> the first time he saw me,</i>

58:12.523 --> 58:14.423
<i> and he said,</i>
<i> "the real Mr. Rogers."</i>

58:14.425 --> 58:17.793
That's, uh,
Mr. Rogers there in the, uh...

58:17.795 --> 58:19.595
-On the left.
-On the left, yeah.

58:19.597 --> 58:20.963
Uh, now, how do you react
to that?

58:20.965 --> 58:23.131
Well, some of them
aren't very funny.

58:23.133 --> 58:26.134
But I think that, uh...
That a lot of them

58:26.136 --> 58:28.437
are done with real kindness

58:28.439 --> 58:29.938
-in their hearts.
-Mm-hmm.

58:29.940 --> 58:32.875
I'm moving to a new
neighborhood

58:32.877 --> 58:35.377
where I've made a...
A new friend.

58:36.780 --> 58:39.348
Can you say "hooker"?

58:39.350 --> 58:41.283
<i> There were some that...</i>

58:41.285 --> 58:43.785
Were not as kind

58:43.787 --> 58:49.725
<i> in nature, and if they</i>
<i> made fun of the philosophy,</i>

58:49.727 --> 58:50.726
<i> that was the only thing</i>

58:50.728 --> 58:53.028
that offended him, I think.

58:53.030 --> 58:56.632
<i> The battle of the pbs stars.</i>

58:56.634 --> 59:00.669
<i> The crowd is literally buzzing</i>
<i> with excitement</i>

59:00.671 --> 59:03.205
<i> as Mr. Rogers enters the ring.</i>

59:03.207 --> 59:04.706
<i> Oh, look out there, Fred!</i>

59:04.708 --> 59:07.309
<i> Fred had such</i>
<i> a great sense of humor,</i>

59:07.311 --> 59:08.977
for the most part.

59:08.979 --> 59:11.213
<i> There's child,</i>
<i> obviously in shape</i>

59:11.215 --> 59:13.482
<i> -and ready for this fight. </i>
-Thank you.

59:13.484 --> 59:14.983
<i> But what about Rogers?</i>

59:14.985 --> 59:19.354
<i> Experts have cast aspersions</i>
<i> on his manhood itself.</i>

59:19.356 --> 59:22.024
<i> Fred would watch them</i>
<i> with the rest of us,</i>

59:22.026 --> 59:25.527
<i> and everybody would be</i>
<i> laughing, and I just wonder...</i>

59:25.529 --> 59:28.730
If a little bit
of fat Freddy came back.

59:30.033 --> 59:32.501
<i> Just before</i>
<i> getting to adolescence,</i>

59:32.503 --> 59:36.838
<i> he didn't have an easy time</i>
<i> making friends, I don't think.</i>

59:36.840 --> 59:40.609
He got a good taste of what
bullying was all about.

59:41.544 --> 59:43.211
<i> I've often wondered,</i>

59:43.213 --> 59:46.181
if there hadn't been
a fat Freddy,

59:46.183 --> 59:48.550
would there have been
a Mr. Rogers?

59:48.552 --> 59:49.851
<i> You can feel the momentum</i>

59:49.853 --> 59:51.853
<i>actually swinging toward child.</i>

59:51.855 --> 59:54.189
<i> And what just happened there?</i>

59:54.191 --> 59:55.557
<i> He grabbed a puppet!</i>

59:55.559 --> 59:57.125
<i> Oh, look at this!</i>

59:57.127 --> 01:00:00.362
<i> He's hitting child</i>
<i> with the lovable king Friday!</i>

01:00:00.364 --> 01:00:02.364
<i> And the French chef is down.</i>

01:00:11.208 --> 01:00:12.407
A laughter record.

01:00:12.409 --> 01:00:16.044
Used to play one like this
when I was a young boy.

01:00:16.046 --> 01:00:18.313
You see, I felt
that the adults around me

01:00:18.315 --> 01:00:21.617
were pressuring me to be
what I couldn't be yet.

01:00:21.619 --> 01:00:24.386
"Act like a grown-up,"
I'd hear them say.

01:00:24.388 --> 01:00:27.756
Well, I was afraid they'd laugh
at me when I tried.

01:00:27.758 --> 01:00:29.891
So I found a record like this,

01:00:29.893 --> 01:00:32.060
and I could make
the laughs start

01:00:32.062 --> 01:00:36.064
and make them stop
whenever I wanted to.

01:00:36.066 --> 01:00:38.734
For someone who hated
to be laughed at,

01:00:38.736 --> 01:00:41.737
it was a good feeling
to be in charge

01:00:41.739 --> 01:00:44.139
of at least this laughter.

01:00:45.842 --> 01:00:52.648
I think that those
who would try

01:00:52.650 --> 01:00:56.585
to make you feel less
than who you are...

01:00:56.587 --> 01:00:58.320
I think that's
the greatest evil.

01:01:15.272 --> 01:01:16.938
<i> There was</i>
<i> a wonderful quote from Fred.</i>

01:01:16.940 --> 01:01:19.174
Oh, that's hard.

01:01:19.176 --> 01:01:21.376
<i> The most important learning--</i>

01:01:21.378 --> 01:01:25.347
it's the ability to accept
and expect mistakes

01:01:25.349 --> 01:01:27.649
and deal with the
disappointment that they bring.

01:01:27.651 --> 01:01:29.451
Hi, neighbor.

01:01:29.453 --> 01:01:32.854
Had a little trouble
with my zipper there.

01:01:32.856 --> 01:01:36.291
I'll get these shoes tied
and then...

01:01:36.293 --> 01:01:38.360
Try the zipper again.

01:01:38.362 --> 01:01:41.029
<i> And Fred also understood</i>

01:01:41.031 --> 01:01:44.800
<i> that there's a deeper level.</i>

01:01:44.802 --> 01:01:46.468
<i> You know something,</i>

01:01:46.470 --> 01:01:48.837
-lady aberlin?
-What, Daniel?

01:01:48.839 --> 01:01:51.840
I've been wondering
about something myself.

01:01:51.842 --> 01:01:53.975
Something about Mr. skunk?

01:01:53.977 --> 01:01:56.311
Something about mistakes.

01:01:56.313 --> 01:01:57.979
What is it?

01:01:57.981 --> 01:02:02.884
I've been wondering
if I was a mistake.

01:02:03.986 --> 01:02:05.821
<i> If you were a mistake?</i>

01:02:05.823 --> 01:02:07.889
And I will tell you,

01:02:07.891 --> 01:02:12.661
sitting in the studio
listening to that, that day,

01:02:12.663 --> 01:02:14.996
I said to myself,

01:02:14.998 --> 01:02:18.266
"i can't believe Fred
had the courage

01:02:18.268 --> 01:02:20.669
to put that into words."

01:02:20.671 --> 01:02:25.841
Sometimes I wonder
if I'm too tame.

01:02:57.141 --> 01:02:58.206
You do?

01:03:01.879 --> 01:03:06.314
<i> Lady aberlin</i>
<i> is saying to Daniel</i>

01:03:06.316 --> 01:03:08.550
what Fred himself
wanted to say,

01:03:08.552 --> 01:03:12.454
not only to his childhood self,
but to all children.

01:03:19.730 --> 01:03:21.129
"Okay, then Daniel's
going to say,

01:03:21.131 --> 01:03:23.131
'oh, thank you.
That helped me a lot.'"

01:03:32.075 --> 01:03:33.575
<i> and I thought to myself,</i>

01:03:33.577 --> 01:03:36.611
<i> "thank you, Fred,</i>
<i> for reminding us</i>

01:03:36.613 --> 01:03:41.516
<i> that it's not so easy</i>
<i> to quiet a doubt."</i>

01:03:41.518 --> 01:03:44.085
But make it a duet

01:03:44.087 --> 01:03:47.155
so that it's not just
your fears,

01:03:47.157 --> 01:03:49.424
but you'll hear my support.

